  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n2 issues with transaction history on mobile network: \r\n\r\n#### 1) When open transaction history for first time, \"Load more\" button doesn't do anything on click.\r\n#### 2) No caching of transaction history in view, so after relogin on m–æbile network (with \"Use mobile data\" = OFF) it is empty again\r\nAlso there is no indication that it should be pull-to-refresh to download transaction history (cc @errorists how to do it in better way)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1) if \"Load more\" button is useless - let's hide it\r\n2) if transaction history was loaded before, assume it should be loaded after relogin.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1) https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/110498872-00499880-80f8-11eb-8603-8503fae1f554.mp4\r\n2) https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/110498884-02abf280-80f8-11eb-8279-cbe86b724817.mp4\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status (on cellular network)\r\n- Restore multiaccount with transaction history\r\n- Tap on \"Load more\" (ISSUE 1)\r\n- Pull-to-refresh\r\n- Relogin and open transaction history (ISSUE 2)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: release 1.12\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n",
